Johannesburg – The department of health said that 13 973 new Covid-19 cases were recorded in the past 24 hours. The cumulative amount of cases in the country now stands at 1 325 659. The department of health further said, “Regrettably, we report a further 384 COVID19 related deaths have been reported. Our recoveries now stand at 1 083 978, representing a recovery rate of 81,7%.” The department said that the number of total deaths is now 36 851.  